U.S. SENIOR OPEN
August 12, 2016
Stephen Ames
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
 Q.  So were you happy with your performance today?  
STEPHEN AMES: It was good.  I didn't hit very well, but I got it around, which was nice.   
 Q.  How did you manage 2 under, then, despite --  
STEPHEN AMES: Short game.  Short game and putting, which you've got to have sometimes when you're not hitting it great.   
 Q.  Sure.  And how are you feeling heading into tomorrow?  Obviously, you have a pretty good score right now.  
STEPHEN AMES: Two days to go, a lot of golf to play, especially around here.  We'll see how the USGA sets up the course the next couple of days.   
 Q.  Were you happy with the conditions?  
STEPHEN AMES: Very good.  Excellent golf course.  Very fun to play.   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT